  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine the potentially beneficial aspects of CCR5
      inhibition on inflammation and endothelial function as measured by brachial artery reactivity
      in antiretroviral treated HIV patients with an undetectable viral load.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
